ZH: 当别人迟到时，不要动怒。
EN: Don't get angry when someone is late.

ZH: 他常常因为生意失败而动怒。
EN: He often gets angry because of business failures.

ZH: 她动怒是因为他们一直打电话给她。
EN: She got angry because they kept calling her.

ZH: 昨天老板动怒了，因为我迟到了。
EN: Yesterday the boss got angry because I was late.

ZH: 他在路上动怒，因为遇到了交通拥堵。
EN: He got angry on the road because of the traffic jam.

ZH: 我在店里动怒，因为服务太差了。
EN: I got angry in the store because the service was terrible.

ZH: 她动怒了，因为我弄脏了她的新裙子。
EN: She got angry because I stained her new dress.

ZH: 孩子通常会因为自己的愿望没有被满足而动怒。
EN: Children usually get angry when their wishes are not fulfilled.

ZH: 他们动怒是因为电话一直忙线。
EN: They got angry because the phone was constantly busy.

ZH: 我妈妈动怒了，因为我忘了做家庭作业。
EN: My mom got angry because I forgot to do my homework.

ZH: 他动怒了，因为对方说了一些侮辱他的话。
EN: He got angry because the other person said something insulting to him.

ZH: 如果你不小心破坏了他的创作，他会动怒。
EN: He will get angry if you accidentally damage his artwork.

ZH: 那个顾客动怒了，因为他们给错了他的订单。
EN: The customer got angry because they gave him the wrong order.

ZH: 他动怒是因为他们一直在嘲笑他。
EN: He got angry because they kept mocking him.

ZH: 如果你打断他的谈话，他会动怒。
EN: He will get angry if you interrupt his conversation.

ZH: 她动怒了，因为她的计划被取消了。
EN: She got angry because her plans got canceled.

ZH: 当遇到困难时，他很容易就动怒了。
EN: He easily gets angry when faced with difficulties.

ZH: 妈妈动怒了，因为孩子们一直闹不停。
EN: Mom got angry because the children kept misbehaving.

ZH: 当别人不尊重他的意见时，他会动怒。
EN: He gets angry when others do not respect his opinions.

ZH: 警察动怒了，因为他们违反了交通规则。
EN: The police got angry because they violated traffic rules.
